edu.uta.cse.fireeye.common

Class SUT

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.uta.cse.fireeye.common.SUT

  • public class SUT
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents the configuration of a System Under Test (SUT). A SUT may contain a list of parameters, relations, constraints, and an existing test set.
    • There are two types of parameters, input and output parameters. Output parameters are used to specify expected outcomes and are useful for test automation. Output parameters are optional.
    • There exists at least one relation in a SUT. If no relation is defined, a default relation will be automatically added.
    • Constraints specify restrictions that must be satisfied by a test. Constraints are optional.
    • An existing test set can be specified to reuse prior test effort. An existing test set may not be t-way complete; in this case, it can be extended by the test generation engine to become a complete t-way test set.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Yu Lei
